## Analysis of the Main Target Image:

### Count & Layers:
- **Block Count:** The structure consists of 16 building blocks.
- **Layers:** The structure has three distinct layers.

### Spatial Relationships:
- **Base Layer:** 
  - Two red arches (blocks) are placed side by side, forming a base.
  - Four orange cylinders are positioned to the right of the arches.
- **Middle Layer:**
  - A yellow rectangular block is placed on top of the left arch.
  - A green rectangular block is placed on top of the right arch.
  - Two green rectangular blocks are placed on top of the orange cylinders.
- **Top Layer:**
  - An orange triangular block is placed on top of the yellow rectangular block.
  - A green rectangular block is placed on top of the other green blocks.
